# Future Enhancements - Implementation Complete ✅

> **Date:** 2025-11-24  
> **Status:** ✅ **ALL 4 FUTURE ENHANCEMENTS FULLY IMPLEMENTED**

---

## Summary

All 4 future enhancement tools have been fully implemented in the `aibos-convention-validation` MCP server (v1.1.0).

---

## ✅ Implemented Tools

### 1. `validate_imports` ✅

**Implementation:**
- AST-based import parsing using @babel/parser
- Validates import statement naming
- Checks package naming (@aibos/* pattern)
- Validates default imports (camelCase)
- Validates named imports (camelCase/PascalCase based on type)

**Status:** ✅ Complete and tested

---

### 2. `validate_code_examples` ✅

**Implementation:**
- Markdown code block parsing
- Language tag validation
- Empty code example detection
- Incomplete example detection
- Long inline code warnings

**Status:** ✅ Complete and tested

---

### 3. `validate_cross_references` ✅

**Implementation:**
- Internal link validation
- Broken reference detection
- Reference-style link validation
- Empty link text detection
- File existence checking

**Status:** ✅ Complete and tested

---

### 4. `validate_docs_structure` ✅

**Implementation:**
- Documentation directory structure validation
- Recommended element checking
- Markdown file validation
- README.md presence checking

**Status:** ✅ Complete and tested

---

